HEADWORD: Garrot
<hw>Gar"rot</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F. Cf.
<er>Garrote</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Surg.)</fld> <def>A stick or small wooden
cylinder used for tightening a bandage, in order to compress the
arteries of a limb.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Garrot</ent>⟦br⟧

